@224 = ~Flame Blade (Evocation)
Level: 2
Sphere: elemental (Fire)
Range: 0
Duration: 4 rounds + 1 round/2 levels
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: special
Saving Throw: none

With this spell, the caster causes a blazing ray of red-hot fire to spring forth from his hand. This blade-like ray is wielded as if it were a sword that the caster already knows how to use, hence there are no bonuses or penalties. If the caster successfully hits with the flame blade, the creature struck suffers 1d8 points of fire damage, +1 every 2 levels of the caster of the spell (up to a maximum 1d8 +10). Of non-material nature, fire dwellers and those using fire as an innate attack form does not suffer it, and does not suffer from strength bonus of the caster. However, it is not a magical weapon in the normal sense of the term, so creatures struck only by magical weapons are not harmed by it.
Flame Blade can't be enchanted by the spell "Blazing Weapon".~
