@2211 = ~Burning Blood~
@2212 = ~Burning Blood (Alteration)
Level 2
Sphere: elemental (Fire)
Range: 30 meters
Duration: 4 rounds
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: Negated

This horrible spell boils the blood of the target creature who would try his saving throw at -2 (-1 extra for every 5 levels of the caster after the 20th). Creatures with no blood (undead, golems, elementals, etc ...) can not be affected by this spell.
At the first round, the blood of the victim begins to warm up and the latter feels in a bad shape and feverish. Second to fourth round, his blood is gaining temperature to burn his internal organs. The effects of the spell are subdivided as follows:
1st round: the victim suffers -1 to his saving throws until the end of the spell.
2nd round: the victim suffers 1D4 damage points
3rd round: the victim suffers 2D4 damage points and -1 to saving throws until the end of the spell.
4th round: the victim suffers 4D4 damage points.~

@2213 = ~Magma Ball~
@2214 = ~Magma Ball (Evocation)
Level: 2
Sphere: elemental (fire)
Range: 0
Duration: instantaneous
Casting Time: 3
Area of Effect: the caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell creates a huge chunk of molten rock that the preacher can throw as a projectile taken as a +1 magical (but it does not give any bonus to hit or damage). If he hits a creature with this ball, it explodes, covering the victim with lava. The latter suffers 1D4 crushing damage and 2D4 burning damage.
Lava will remain warm after the impact for 1 round every 3 level of the spellcaster for a maximum of 6 rounds at level 18 (half if the target makes a successful saving throw vs. spells) and inflicts 2D4 burning damage at every round. After which it cools down, crumbles and turns into dust.~
